  "text": "Synthetic biology tools (e.g. gene expression circuits, CRISPR/Cas-based systems) are often distributed between multiple plasmid vectors at different copy numbers in order to synthesise each component at the required concentration [CITATION_1] . The large RSF1010 vector is able to replicate in a broad range of microbes including gram-negative bacteria such as E. coli and several cyanobacterial species.",
